And when you hear some
of these Tibetan monks

00:54:27.560 --> 00:54:29.800 align:middle line:84%
that are over here from
the Gyuto monastery

00:54:29.800 --> 00:54:32.800 align:middle line:84%
outside of Lhasa, when
they sing the aums,

00:54:32.800 --> 00:54:34.480 align:middle line:84%
you know what it
means, all right.

00:54:34.480 --> 00:54:41.940 align:middle line:90%


00:54:41.940 --> 00:54:45.060 align:middle line:84%
That's the zoom of
being in the world.

00:54:45.060 --> 00:54:50.410 align:middle line:90%


00:54:50.410 --> 00:54:54.970 align:middle line:84%
And to be in touch with that and
to get the sense of that, that

00:54:54.970 --> 00:54:57.190 align:middle line:90%
is the peak experience of all.

00:54:57.190 --> 00:55:02.481 align:middle line:90%


00:55:02.481 --> 00:55:06.840 align:middle line:84%
Ah, ooh, mm, the birth,
the coming into being,

00:55:06.840 --> 00:55:10.300 align:middle line:84%
and the dissolution,
the cycle of that.

00:55:10.300 --> 00:55:16.150 align:middle line:84%
And this is called the
four element syllable.

00:55:16.150 --> 00:55:18.634 align:middle line:90%
What is the fourth element?

00:55:18.634 --> 00:55:24.480 align:middle line:84%
Ah, ooh, mm, and the silence
out of which it comes,

00:55:24.480 --> 00:55:28.080 align:middle line:84%
back into which it goes,
and which underlies it.

00:55:28.080 --> 00:55:31.350 align:middle line:90%
Now, my life is the ah, ooh, mm.

00:55:31.350 --> 00:55:34.440 align:middle line:84%
But there is a silence
that underlies it,

00:55:34.440 --> 00:55:39.450 align:middle line:84%
and that is what we
would call the immortal.

00:55:39.450 --> 00:55:42.150 align:middle line:84%
This is the mortal, and
that's the immortal.

00:55:42.150 --> 00:55:45.780 align:middle line:84%
And there wouldn't be this
if there weren't that.

00:55:45.780 --> 00:55:48.660 align:middle line:84%
>> The meaning is
essentially wordless.

00:55:48.660 --> 00:55:49.740 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:55:49.740 --> 00:55:54.450 align:middle line:84%
Well, words are always
qualifications and limitations.

00:55:54.450 --> 00:55:58.440 align:middle line:84%
>> And yet, Joe, all we puny
human beings are left with is

00:55:58.440 --> 00:56:01.080 align:middle line:84%
this miserable language,
beautiful though it is,

00:56:01.080 --> 00:56:04.170 align:middle line:84%
that falls short of
trying to describe--

00:56:04.170 --> 00:56:05.190 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:56:05.190 --> 00:56:07.350 align:middle line:84%
And that's why it's
a peak experience

00:56:07.350 --> 00:56:14.290 align:middle line:84%
to break past all that every
